abstract: James Thomas Hodgkinson, 66, of Belleville, Ill., who died after a shootout with the police, had traveled to Washington in recent weeks to protest, his brother said.
snippet: James Thomas Hodgkinson, 66, of Belleville, Ill., who died after a shootout with the police, had traveled to Washington in recent weeks to protest, his brother said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — He lived out of his van in the Northern Virginia suburbs and took showers at the Y.M.C.A. On Facebook, he posted furious criticism of President Trump and pledged allegiance to Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont. Back home in Illinois, neighbors complained to the police of his practicing his shooting near their home.

headline_main: Virginia Shooting Suspect Was Distraught Over Trump’s Election, Brother Says
headline_print_headline: Furious at Trump and Unhappy  With ‘Way Things Were Going’

abstract: A gunman opened fired as Republican members of a congressional baseball team held a practice. He was killed in a shootout.
snippet: A gunman opened fired as Republican members of a congressional baseball team held a practice. He was killed in a shootout.
lead_paragraph: ALEXANDRIA, Va. — A lone gunman who was said to be distraught over President Trump’s election opened fire on members of the Republican congressional baseball team at a practice field in this Washington suburb on Wednesday, using a rifle to shower the field with bullets that struck four people, including Steve Scalise, the majority whip of the House of Representatives.

abstract: Marc E. Kasowitz, the president’s private lawyer, has counseled administration staff and exerted broader influence over legal strategy.
snippet: Marc E. Kasowitz, the president’s private lawyer, has counseled administration staff and exerted broader influence over legal strategy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A new figure has swept through the West Wing lately, a man with silver hair combed back across his head, rimless glasses perched on his nose, a white handkerchief tucked neatly into his suit pocket, a taste for legal pugilism and an uncertain role in a building confronted by a host of political and legal threats.

abstract: Israel’s capture of Jerusalem’s Old City 50 years ago changed the region. But the dilemma about its occupation of Palestinian areas remains unsolved.
snippet: Israel’s capture of Jerusalem’s Old City 50 years ago changed the region. But the dilemma about its occupation of Palestinian areas remains unsolved.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — The six days of the 1967 war were the most important — triumphant, even — in modern Israeli history. But after 50 years, Israel is still struggling with them.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The campaign ad appeared during the presidential contest of 2008. Rapid-fire images of belching smokestacks and melting ice sheets were followed by a soothing narrator who praised a candidate who had stood up to President George W. Bush and “sounded the alarm on global warming.”

abstract: Twenty-five years after luxury labels sued his Harlem boutique out of existence, Gucci looks to him for inspiration.
snippet: Twenty-five years after luxury labels sued his Harlem boutique out of existence, Gucci looks to him for inspiration.
lead_paragraph: The Harlem couturier Daniel Day, better known as Dapper Dan, was all over social media last week after Gucci unveiled a jacket that looked very much like one he designed nearly three decades ago for the Olympic sprinter Diane Dixon.

abstract: The event, the Senior P.G.A. Championship, illustrates the pitfalls associated with a president unwilling to make a clean break with his commercial empire.
snippet: The event, the Senior P.G.A. Championship, illustrates the pitfalls associated with a president unwilling to make a clean break with his commercial empire.
lead_paragraph: STERLING, Va. — On the green at the 11th hole, the golf stars John Daly and Rocco Mediate sized up their opening tournament putts. Nearby, a Golf Channel crew swung its cameras into place. And a pack of spectators lined up to watch it all.
